================================================================
Fix: Schedules duplicated in Lakebase global_config JSONB blob
================================================================

Context:
- The Volume backend stores schedules *inside* the
  ``.global_config.json`` blob (legitimate, single-file storage).
- The Lakebase backend has a dedicated ``schedules`` table, so
  the JSONB ``global_config.config`` column must stay free of any
  ``schedules`` (or ``schedule_history``) key.
- The Volume â†’ Lakebase migration helper was forwarding the
  whole Volume blob â€” including ``schedules`` â€” to
  ``dst.save_global_config`` *and* then calling ``save_schedules``,
  duplicating the data into both the JSONB column and the
  ``schedules`` table. Subsequent ``save_global_config`` calls
  preserved the duplicated key (only ``schedule_history`` was
  stripped), so the corruption was sticky.

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py
   - ``load_global_config`` now strips both ``schedules`` and
     ``schedule_history`` from the returned blob (uses the
     pre-existing but unused ``_SCHEDULES_KEY`` constant).
   - ``save_global_config`` filters ``schedules`` /
     ``schedule_history`` out of *updates* before merging and
     drops them from the loaded data, so the persisted JSONB
     can never reacquire those keys.
   - ``initialize`` now calls a new ``_scrub_global_config_legacy_keys``
     helper that runs an idempotent ``UPDATE â€¦ SET config =
     (config - 'schedules') - 'schedule_history' WHERE config ?
     'schedules' OR config ? 'schedule_history'``. Existing
     deployments self-heal at next app start; the WHERE clause
     keeps the operation a no-op afterwards.

2. src/back/objects/registry/store/migration.py
   - ``migrate_volume_to_lakebase`` strips ``schedules`` /
     ``schedule_history`` from the Volume blob before calling
     ``dst.save_global_config``. Defensive (the Lakebase store
     also strips them now) but makes the intent explicit and
     avoids growing the JSONB row needlessly during migration.

