================================================================
Migrate to Lakebase: hide when redundant, warn on overwrite
================================================================

Three regimes for the *Migrate to Lakebase* button on the admin
Registry Location page:

1. **Lakebase active backend + tables populated** â†’ hide the
   button. Re-running the migration there silently overwrites
   live rows and offering it without context is a footgun.

2. **Volume active backend + Lakebase tables populated** â†’ keep
   the button visible but downgrade to *Re-sync from Volume*:
   ``btn-outline-danger`` style + a hard confirmation popup
   spelling out the overwrite ("Continue only if you intend to
   reset Lakebase from the Volume snapshot"). This is the
   legitimate reset path for admins who deliberately want to
   throw away post-migration changes.

3. **Otherwise** (Volume + empty Lakebase, or Lakebase but
   uninitialised) â†’ standard *Migrate to Lakebase* CTA with the
   informational popup.

Detection is driven by a new ``populated`` boolean in the
Lakebase runtime payload. ``_lakebase_runtime_info`` now calls a
single consolidated probe ``_lakebase_schema_status`` that
returns ``{initialized, populated}`` from one store instance.
``populated`` is true iff any of the canonical data tables
(``domains``, ``permission_sets``, ``scheduled_builds``,
``scheduled_history``) carries one or more rows. Any failure â€”
psycopg missing, connection error, ``table_row_counts`` raising
on a permissions issue â€” degrades gracefully to ``False`` so
the admin UI keeps rendering.

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   - New ``_lakebase_schema_status`` helper returning
     ``{initialized, populated}``.
   - ``_lakebase_schema_initialized`` is now a thin wrapper
     delegating to the status probe (kept for backwards
     compatibility with callers that only need the boolean).
   - ``_lakebase_runtime_info`` surfaces ``populated`` next to
     ``initialized`` in the payload.

2. src/front/static/registry/js/registry.js
   - ``updateBackendChooser`` toggles the migrate button between
     hidden / *Migrate* / *Re-sync from Volume* using
     ``lakebase.populated``. Stores the regime in
     ``btn.dataset.mode`` so the click handler can branch.
   - Click handler picks one of two confirmation dialogs: an
     informational migrate prompt or a red, explicit overwrite
     warning ("Re-sync from Volume â€” overwrite Lakebase?").
   - Finally-block restore now respects the entered mode so a
     failed re-sync no longer reverts the label to *Migrate to
     Lakebase*.

3. tests/test_settings_lakebase_status.py (new)
   Seven cases pinning the probe behaviour: psycopg-missing
   short-circuit, uninitialised schema skips the row probe,
   empty tables report ``populated=False``, any non-empty
   canonical table reports ``populated=True``, factory failure
   is swallowed, ``table_row_counts`` failure keeps
   ``initialized=True`` while reporting ``populated=False``,
   and ``_lakebase_schema_initialized`` delegates correctly.

