[18:55] Fix Lakebase "0 rows / not initialized" when SP lacks USAGE
â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€

Symptom (post-Autoscaling-cleanup redeploy of ontobricks-dev): the
admin Registry Location panel reported every table as 0 rows and
"ontobricks_registry not initialized â€” run Migrate to Lakebase or
initialize the registry", even though the schema held 9 domains,
10 versions, 1 registry row, etc.

Root cause: the ``ontobricks-dev`` service principal was created
with zero privileges on the ``ontobricks_registry`` schema (owner
was the human admin). Without ``USAGE``, ``to_regclass`` returns
NULL even when the table exists, and ``information_schema.tables``
filters out everything the SP can't see â€” so ``is_initialized``
silently returned False and ``table_row_counts`` returned 0 for
every requested table. The previous code logged the failure at
DEBUG only, which is invisible in the Apps runtime.

Fix:

1. src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py
   - New ``init_status() -> {initialized, reason, error}`` method
     replacing the silent boolean. Probes are explicit:
     Â· ``has_schema_privilege(current_user, schema, 'USAGE')`` â†’
       ``no_usage`` with an actionable error message that names
       the bootstrap script;
     Â· ``to_regclass(schema.registries) IS NOT NULL`` â†’
       ``no_registries_table``;
     Â· ``_fetch_registry_id()`` â†’ ``no_registry_row``;
     Â· success â†’ ``ok``;
     Â· any exception â†’ ``connect_failed`` (logged at WARNING).
   - ``is_initialized()`` is now a thin wrapper over
     ``init_status()['initialized']``, preserving the base
     contract.

2. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   - ``lakebase_stats_result`` returns the new ``reason`` token
     and surfaces ``init_status['error']`` as ``message`` so the
     UI can render the precise cause.
   - ``_lakebase_schema_status`` table list fixed: replaced the
     stale ``permission_sets`` / ``scheduled_builds`` /
     ``scheduled_history`` (none of which exist in the Lakebase
     schema) with the real names ``domain_versions``,
     ``domain_permissions``, ``schedules``, ``schedule_runs``.
     Without this fix, ``populated`` was always False because
     none of the requested tables were on the
     ``_KNOWN_TABLES`` whitelist.

3. src/front/static/registry/js/registry.js
   - Reason-aware copy in the Lakebase Stats panel:
     Â· ``no_usage``      â†’ red shield + "service principal lacks
                           USAGE â€¦ run scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-
                           perms.sh";
     Â· ``connect_failed`` / ``table_count_failed`` â†’ red X +
                           the underlying error;
     Â· ``no_registry_row`` â†’ amber + "click *Initialize*";
     Â· default              â†’ existing "not initialized" copy.

4. scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh (new)
   - Idempotent bootstrap that mints a Lakebase JWT for the
     calling human user, looks up each app's
     ``service_principal_client_id``, and runs the canonical
     GRANT block:
     Â· ``USAGE, CREATE`` on the schema;
     Â· ``SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE`` on every existing table;
     Â· ``USAGE, SELECT, UPDATE`` on every existing sequence
       (bigserial PKs in ``schedule_runs``);
     Â· same set as ``ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES`` so future tables
