## Fix Registry/Browse not auto-loading the domain list on first page open

Context: Opening ``/registry`` (Browse tab) showed only the "Loading
domains..." placeholder until the user clicked the Refresh button. Root
cause: ``registry.js`` is shared between the Settings â†’ Registry tab
and the Registry/Browse page. ``updateRegistryLabel()`` writes to
``#registryLocationLabel``, an element that exists *only* on the
Settings page. On the Browse page ``label`` was ``null`` and the
``label.innerHTML = â€¦`` line threw a ``TypeError``, which the
``loadRegistryConfig`` ``try``/``catch`` swallowed before reaching
``updateRegistryStatus()`` â€” the path that actually calls
``loadRegistryDomains()``. The Refresh button worked because its
handler bypasses the init flow and calls ``loadRegistryDomains()``
directly. Two-layer fix (Fowler "Introduce Guard Clause" +
defence-in-depth wrapping).

Changes:

1. src/front/static/registry/js/registry.js
   - ``updateRegistryLabel``: bail out early when
     ``#registryLocationLabel`` is absent (Browse page) â€” guard
     clause prevents the TypeError that was masking the entire
     post-fetch chain.
   - ``loadRegistryConfig``: wrap the three cosmetic helpers
     (``updateBackendChooser``/``updateLakebasePanel``/``updateRegistryLabel``)
     in a ``_safe`` shim that logs and continues, so a future
     regression in any one of them no longer prevents
     ``updateRegistryStatus`` from triggering the domain-list
     auto-load.

