## Default registry backend is now Lakebase when the resource is bound

Context: After the autoscaling-only redeploy several admins were left on
the Volume backend even though the ``database`` resource was bound and
the ``lakebase`` extra was installed â€” the only path to flip them was
to manually toggle the radio in Settings â†’ Registry. ``REGISTRY_BACKEND``
was a literal ``volume`` default, so unless the operator explicitly
exported ``REGISTRY_BACKEND=lakebase`` (and they rarely did, because the
chooser exists) Lakebase-bound deployments still defaulted to JSON-on-
Volume. This made fresh ``ontobricks-dev`` deployments report "0 rows /
not initialised" until somebody noticed the radio.

New behaviour: a new ``"auto"`` sentinel is the default for
``Settings.registry_backend`` (``REGISTRY_BACKEND=auto``). At resolution
time ``resolve_default_backend`` picks Lakebase when *both* the
``psycopg`` extra and the PG* env vars are present, and falls back to
Volume otherwise. Operators can still pin either backend explicitly with
``REGISTRY_BACKEND=volume`` / ``REGISTRY_BACKEND=lakebase``, and the UI
choice (radio) keeps the highest priority â€” flipping to Volume on a
Lakebase-bound app stays sticky exactly like before.

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/registry/RegistryService.py
   - Added module-level ``_lakebase_runtime_available()`` probe and
     ``resolve_default_backend(raw)`` policy function. Single source of
     truth for the "auto" â†’ ``volume`` / ``lakebase`` mapping, no
     dependency on the FastAPI service layer (so the scheduler
     subprocess can call it).
   - ``RegistryCfg.from_domain`` now routes ``settings.registry_backend``
     and the session-saved ``backend`` through the resolver. ``"auto"``
     stored in either layer no longer silently freezes on Volume.
   - ``RegistryCfg.from_dict`` shares the same resolver so dicts that
     omit ``backend`` (or set it to ``"auto"``) inherit the runtime
     default rather than the dataclass literal.

2. src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py
   - ``BuildScheduler._resolve_creds`` calls ``resolve_default_backend``
     instead of defaulting to ``"volume"``. Schedulers restored at
     startup now match the live request path on a Lakebase-bound app.

3. src/back/objects/registry/__init__.py
   - Re-exported ``resolve_default_backend`` for callers (and tests).

4. src/shared/config/settings.py
   - ``Settings.registry_backend`` default flipped from ``"volume"`` to
     ``"auto"``. Updated docstring describes the policy and points at
     ``resolve_default_backend``.

5. .env.example
   - Updated the ``REGISTRY_BACKEND`` example to advertise ``auto``
     (default), ``volume``, ``lakebase``.

6. tests/test_registry.py
   - New ``TestResolveDefaultBackend`` class (7 cases) covering pass-
     through, unknown values, ``auto``/empty/None/case-insensitive
     resolution with both runtime-available and runtime-missing
     branches.
   - New ``TestRegistryCfgFromDomainAuto`` class (4 cases) covering the
     end-to-end flow: ``Settings.registry_backend = "auto"`` resolution
     with/without Lakebase runtime, UI Volume pin beats auto default,
     ``"auto"`` saved in the session inherits runtime resolution.
   - Both classes patch the module-level probe via ``sys.modules`` to
     dodge the package-init shadowing of the ``RegistryService``
     submodule (the homonymous re-exported class wins attribute
     lookups on the package).

